# Module: `packages/element`

- Element types are immutable for **external** use — never mutate them directly from outside this package
- Internal, controlled mutations may only be performed via `mutateElement()` — this is the sole sanctioned mutation path inside the package; callers receive a new or updated element reference and must not bypass this contract
- Do not add rendering logic here — rendering belongs in `packages/excalidraw`

## How to verify

```bash
# Direct property assignments outside of mutateElement should not appear.
# (Excludes files that define or call mutateElement itself.)
grep -rn "\.x =\|\.y =\|\.width =\|\.height =" packages/element/src/ \
  | grep -v "mutateElement"

# No rendering code should exist in this package:
grep -rn "renderScene\|canvas\b\|ctx\." packages/element/src/ \
  | grep -v "__tests__\|\.test\."

# Run element-specific tests:
yarn test:app packages/element
```
